args: What do you think of THIS?!
You've gotten really good, Lowen.\nI'm impressed.
It's all thanks to your training.
I'm strong enough to take on any enemies\nthat come my way now!
I'm not afraid of anything anymore.\nNot afraid...of anything...
Oh man, I've gotta go to the bathroom.\nAnd I've come this far, but...
Aaaugh! I can't do this on my own!
You can do this, Lowen. You can do this!\nOkay, here I go!
Uh oh. Where's this? Am I...lost?
AAAUUGH! Wait, no. That's just the wind.\nStupid wind! That's not nice!
I sure hope that isn't talking about me...
Okay, this is all super weird, but I don't\nhave a choice... I have to fight!
Okay, he's gone now. Boy, I sure hope he\ndoesn't catch a cold.
He gave me a heck of a shock, though.\nGlad he wasn't some kind of monster.
...Huh? I can hear footsteps again.\nIs that you, Ranzal?
Wait, that's not Ranzal. But then,\nwho IS it?
A fiend? A ghost? How should I attack it?\n...H-hey! You! Stop right there!
Eeeek! I can't take it any moooore!
Yes, it's me. I heard someone yelling out\nhere and came to see what was going on.
What're you doing out here at this hour?
Uh oh. Did you get lost?
You know what? Never mind. Let me just\ntake you there right now.
You're welcome. Honestly, I'm glad I made\nit in time.
Yeah. But still, I can't believe I couldn't\neven go to the bathroom by myself...
I thought I was stronger, but I'm still just\nas weak as ever.
That's not true at all, Lowen.\nYou're absolutely getting stronger.
But strength comes in many forms.
Such as the strength to fight, or the\nstrength to not give in to our fears.
And I think it's good for a person to learn\nmany different strengths.
You bet. No one just starts out not being\nafraid of anything, after all.
So you should just work hard and get\nstronger a little bit at a time.
If you do that, the number of things that\nfrighten you will decrease, and you'll be\nable to protect the people you love.
You know what? You can leave me here.\nI think I'm gonna be fine.
I'm off, then. Have a good night, Lowen.
Oh man, he's SOOO cool! I wanna be like\nhim someday.
I'm gonna work even harder to not just be\nthe little brother anymore!
